706476f-a.text:
Richardson Street, (right) east from Meeker Avenue. Also seen is Meeker Avenue (left) east from Manhattan Avenue
Aug. 13, 1938.
P. L. Sperr

705660f-a.text:
Meeker Avenue, south side, east of Manhattan Avenue. The house partially seen in the right foreground is No. 24 Meeker Avenue. The intersecting street in the foreground is Graham Avenue.
August 13, 1938
P. L. Sperr
705660f-a.folder: Meeker Avenue & Manhattan Avenue, Brooklyn, NY

705661f-a.text:
Meeker Avenue, adjoining the southeast corner of Manhattan Avenue, showing one of the few remaining very old homes in this area. In 1886 this area was part of the Judge William Conselyea property.
P. L. Sperr
August 13, 1938
